We all know Saffron is precious, but what makes it so powerful?​
​
Crocus sativus, the Saffron crocus, blooms only once a year – under intense sun exposure, freezing nights and dry winds. This triggers a survival response in the plant, stimulating the production of vitamins and antioxidants in epic concentrations​
​
And Saffron performs in skin care just like it does in the wild🧡​
​

Happy Earth Day!🌏 ​

A friend of Ayurveda is a friend of the Earth🤝​

In every way, from our holistic ethos to our botanical formulations, as an Ayurvedic Beauty brand, we believe in working with nature – not against it. At KAMA AYURVEDA, we honour beauty with purpose. That’s why, with our formulations, we promise: ​

🌱 90-100% natural origin ingredient formulations
♻️ 100% recycled and recyclable packaging
💚 Ingredients and harvesting processes that protect biodiversity

We’re also proud to be a Butterfly Mark certified brand (@positiveluxury) – a global symbol for luxury brands that meet the highest standards of sustainability.

And our work is never finished. ​

Join us today in celebrating Earth Day, and tell us:
What does a life more aligned with the natural world look like for you? 👇
